  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are in heavy short gamma territory with SPX at 6499.31 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6475 (-9.3B) and the resistance at 6525 (+938M), creating a volatile squeeze zone where any directional move will be amplified by dealer hedging flows. The breakout regime with -5.9B total GEX means dealers are buying this rally and will continue to chase higher if we break above 6525, while any pullback toward 6475 will trigger aggressive dealer buying that should provide strong support. Watch for explosive moves as we're sandwiched between these critical levels - break above 6525 targets the 6550 amplifying wall, while failure to hold above 6475 could trigger cascading dealer selling below the GEX flip at 6407.",
